  "prompt": "What if Obama dies before Trump is inaugurated? Would Joe Biden assume presidency or Trump take oath earlier than planned?",
  "response": "If Barack Obama were to pass away before Donald Trump's inauguration on January 20, 2017, the line of succession as outlined in the U.S. Constitution and the Presidential Succession Act would dictate what happens next. Here's how it would unfold:\n\n1. **Vice President Joe Biden** would immediately become the acting President. As Vice President, Biden is first in the presidential line of succession and would assume the role until the inauguration date.\n\n2. **Donald Trump's Inauguration** would still occur as scheduled on January 20, 2017. Biden would serve as acting President only until that date, at which point Trump would take the oath of office and officially become the 45th President of the United States.\n\nThere is no provision for Donald Trump to take office earlier than January 20, as that date is set by the Constitution (20th Amendment). The transition of power would occur as planned, with Biden temporarily filling the role until Trump is sworn in.",
